Operation Sonnenwende - German offensive to relieve Pomerania from Russian forces and halt advance on Berlin, February 1945.
Operation Attila - Turkish invasion and occupation of northern Cyprus, 1974.
Operation Attila  - German seizure and occupation of Vichy France, 1940.
Operation Eagle - German air offensive against Britain, as a prelude to Seelöwe, 1940.
Operation Bodenplatte - German aerial attack on 27 Allied airbases in Europe, January 1945.
Herkules - Planned Axis airborne invasion of Malta, 1942.
Operation Typhoon - German winter offensive to capture Moscow, in 1941
Operation Fruhingserwachen  - Last German counterattack against Russian forces in Hungary, March 1945.
Operation Rösselsprung - German attempt to capture partisan leader Tito at his Bosnian HQ, May 1944.
Operation Nordwind - German offensive in the Alsace region, January 1945.
Operation Margarethe  -- German operation to keep Hungary from falling to Russia and defecting to the Allies, in March 1944.
Operation Fall Weiss - German invasion of Poland 1939.
